
[1]bursar

   BURS'AR, n. [See Burse.] A treasurer,or cash-keeper, as the bursar of a
   college, or of a monastery; a purser.

   1. A student to whom a stipend is paid out of a burse or fund
   appropriated for that purpose, as the exhibitioners sent to the
   universities in Scotland by each presbytery.
